Global Propylene Glycol Monomethyl Ether Acetate (PMA) Market Insights
Propylene Glycol Monomethyl Ether Acetate (PMA) Market size was valued at USD 1.2 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 1.9 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 6.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Propylene Glycol Monomethyl Ether Acetate (PMA) Market Overview
The Propylene Glycol Monomethyl Ether Acetate (PMA) market has shown significant growth in recent years, driven by increasing demand from industries such as paints and coatings, pharmaceuticals, and electronics. The market size was valued at approximately USD 1.5 billion in 2023 and is expected to grow at a CAGR of 6.8% over the forecast period. This growth is attributed to PMA's solvent properties, which make it a popular choice for various applications including cleaning, degreasing, and manufacturing of consumer goods. The growing adoption of eco-friendly chemicals and the demand for high-performance solvents are expected to further boost market growth. Geographically, North America and Europe hold the largest market shares, but the Asia Pacific region is anticipated to witness the fastest growth due to rapid industrialization and increasing product consumption in countries like China and India.

